+### Noisy git wrapper
+
+A git wrapper on PATH may write progress to stdout even with `--quiet`. That noise
+must not leak into the generated script (stdout); it goes to stderr instead, and
+git failures still propagate.
+
+```zsh
+% # mock a git wrapper that ignores --quiet and writes progress to stdout
+% function git { echo "WRAPPER: git progress noise"; mockgit "$@" }
+% # stdout stays clean when cloning
+% antidote-script --kind clone fakeuser/fakerepo 2>/dev/null
+%
+```
+
+```zsh
+% # wrapper progress is redirected to stderr
+% antidote-script --kind clone bar/foo 2>&1 >/dev/null
+# antidote cloning bar/foo...
+WRAPPER: git progress noise
+%
+```
+
+```zsh
+% # generated script contains only plugin-loading commands
+% rm -rf $ANTIDOTE_HOME/fakeuser
+% antidote-script fakeuser/fakerepo 2>/dev/null | subenv ANTIDOTE_HOME
+fpath+=( "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/fakeuser/fakerepo" )
+source "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/fakeuser/fakerepo/fakerepo.plugin.zsh"
+%
+```
+
+```zsh
+% # git failures still propagate
+% function git { echo "WRAPPER: fatal"; return 128 }
+% antidote-script --kind clone zed/nope 2>/dev/null  #=> --exit 1
+% antidote-script zed/nope &>/dev/null  #=> --exit 1
+% # restore mock git
+% function git { mockgit "$@" }
+%
+```
